value: *There are no Census Block Groups in our sample that have housing units that use coal or coke for heat

command.value:
/*
	*Coal or Coke
	file write myfile "\hspace{4ex} Coal or coke"
	est restore red_perc_coalcokeheat
	mat b=e(mean)
	file write myfile " & " %4.2f (b[1,1]) " & " %4.2f (b[1,2])
	
	matrix input p = (`pperc_coalcokeheat')
	file write myfile " & " %4.2f (p[1, 1])
		if abs(`pperc_coalcokeheat') < 0.05 file write myfile "\$^{*}"
		else if abs(`pperc_coalcokeheat') < 0.01 file write myfile "\$^{**}"
		file write myfile " \\" _n
		
		*/

=.value: "\footnotesize Note: Columns (1) and (2) report average values. Columns (3) reports the p-values of the differences in means."
" P-values reflect clustering at the census block group level."
" All variables are at the Census block group level and come from the American Community Survey 5-year estimates (2007-2011). \\"
